## babylon azure storage get-all
Add the following key in your `config/deployments/deploy.yml` file 
```yaml
# Storage account name
storage_account_name: "..."
```
Containers status can be checked with the following ``az cli`` command
```bash
az storage container list --account-name "..." --output table
```

# Commands
```bash
babylon azure storage get-all
```
Should display the newly created container with it's url
```bash
babylon azure storage --account [account_name] get-all
babylon azure storage --url [account_url] get-all
```
It is possible to use the --account or --url option to specify another storage account